text: Norma Wilson (born 14 September 1929 in Colac, Victoria, Australia) is an Australian former cricket player. Wilson played three tests for the Australia national women's cricket team. ==References== Category:1929 births Category:Australia women Test cricketers Category:Living people Category:People from Colac, Victoria Category:Cricketers from Victoria (Australia)
